# [smallcaps]{[color]{gunmetal}{Macros}}

Macros are programmable action bar buttons that allow players to customize their user-interface and create advanced interactions. Common use cases include combining spells with messages, creating spells with prepared input, and adding buttons for opening the inventory and other screens on mobile devices.

### [smallcaps]{[color]{gunmetal}{Chat commands}}
[code]{/say Prepare to be shrunk!
/cast Shrink}
[br]
[table]{equalcells}
[thead]{Chat commands}{Channel}
[tbody]{`/say` or `/s`}{Say}
[tbody]{`/emote`, `/em`, `/me`, or `/e`}{*Emote*}
[tbody]{`/ooc` or `/o`}{(Out-of-character)}

When using a chat command, the message following the command will be send to its associated channel. Any line not starting with `/` or `#` will be send as a message to the local chat channel.

### [smallcaps]{[color]{gunmetal}{Use items}}
[table]{equalcells, noborder}
[tbody]{[code]{/use Sol Talisman
/use Crown, Coin Toss}}

[table]{equalcells, noborder}
[tbody]{[code]{/use <base item name> [, <action name>]
/use <equipment slot id> [, <action name>]
/use <inventory coordinates> [, <action name>]}}{Uses the given item. An optional action name can be given to use a specific action from the standard dropdown}

[table]{equalcells}
[thead]{Examples}{Description}
[tbody]{`/use 0`}{Any one whole number will be treated as an equipment slot id and will use the item located in the given equipment slot}
[tbody]{`/use 0 0`}{Any two whole numbers will be treated as inventory coordinates and will use the item located at the given inventory coordinates. `0 0` is the top-left position in the inventory, and the heirloom container starts at `0 5`}
[tbody]{`/use Chromatic Dye`}{Base item names will use the first available item with that base}
[tbody]{`/use Onahole(99239)`}{You can add a numeric item id between `()` immediately after the base item name to specify an exact item with the base name to use}

The base name of an item is the name of the item without any prefixes or suffixes caused by enchantments and other properties.

Clicking an item using the Left Mouse Button while holding down the Shift key, or pressing the input field while holding an item will insert its base name. Items that don't stack and cannot be sold or bought in bulk on the item market will also have their id added.

###### [smallcaps]{[color]{gunmetal}{When no action is given — Mouse or touch input}}
* If the item only has one action and it's labelled `Use`, it will attempt to use the action. 
* If the item has any actions not labelled `Use`, it will show the standard dropdown.

###### [smallcaps]{[color]{gunmetal}{When no action is given — Key input}}
* It will attempt to use the action labelled `Use`.

