### [smallcaps]{[color]{gunmetal}{Spellcasting}}
[table]{equalcells, noborder}
[tbody]{[code]{/cast Breast Enlargement
/cast Impair Speech: Bimbo
/cast Change Name, Bimbo
/cast Restore Self (Immediate)}}

[table]{equalcells, noborder}
[tbody]{[code]{/cast <fully qualified spell name> [, <input>]}}{Casts the spell with the given name and optional input}
[tbody]{[code]{/cast Use Pussy(99239)}}{You can add a numeric item id between `()` immediately after the spell name to target an item-specific spell or action}

Clicking a spell using the Left Mouse Button while holding down the Shift key, or pressing the input field while holding a spell will insert the fully qualified name of the spell.

[color]{bronze}{A macro will stop computing after it attempts to cast a spell, so make sure you place any other commands and messages before}

###### [smallcaps]{[color]{gunmetal}{Change Name}}
[code]{/cast Change Name, <new name>}
* If no new name is given, you will be prompted to write a new name when the spell is cast.
* If a new name is given, it will attempt to cast the spell with the new name as input.
* The spell will fail if the input is an invalid name.

###### [smallcaps]{[color]{gunmetal}{Change Height}}
[code]{/cast Change Height, <new height>}
* If no new height is given, you will be prompted to select a new height when the spell is cast.
* If a new height is given, it will attempt to cast the spell with the new height as input.
* Input will clamp to lowest and highest possible height if outside the valid range.
* Input can be `x` for centimeters or `x'y"` for feet and inches.

###### [smallcaps]{[color]{gunmetal}{Transform Item}}
[code]{/cast Transform Item [, <base item name | equipment slot id | inventory coordinates>, <option name>]}
* If no input is given or no item is found, it will open the Transform Item screen normally.
* If an option name is given, it will attempt to immediately transform the item using an option matching the name.

###### [smallcaps]{[color]{gunmetal}{Enchant Item}}
[code]{/cast Enchant Item [, <base item name | equipment slot id | inventory coordinates>]}
* If no input is given or no item is found, opens the Enchant Item screen normally.

###### [smallcaps]{[color]{gunmetal}{Conjure Item}}
[code]{/cast Conjure Item [, <base item name | equipment slot id>, <appearance>, <accessory>, <color>]}
* If no input is given or no item or equipment slot is found, opens the Conjure Item screen normally.
* If an appearance is given, it will attempt to immediately conjure an item with the given appearance and optional accessory and color input.
* The accessory and color input can be given out of order, allowing you to list a color input before or without an accessory input.
* The appearance, accessory, and color input must match an option available to you. `Mark` and `Symbol` can be omitted from accessory input.
* Items that aren't equipped are ignored.

### [smallcaps]{[color]{gunmetal}{Target modifiers}}

You can add target modifiers after the command within `[]` to change the target of the action.

[table]{equalcells, noborder}
[tbody]{[code]{/cast [@player] Enlarge}}{Cast Enlarge on yourself}
[tbody]{[code]{/cast [@opponent] Enlarge}}{Cast Enlarge on your opponent}

[details]{[smallcaps]{[color]{gunmetal}{###### List of target modifiers}}}{
[table]{equalcells}
[thead]{Target modifier}{Description}
[tbody]{`@player`}{Target your character}
[tbody]{`@opponent`}{Target your opponent}
[tbody]{`@owner`}{Target your owner}
[tbody]{`@mouseover`}{Target the character underneath the mouse cursor}}

By default, spells with a target will attempt to target your opponent before you. Spells dragged to an action bar from the spell list targeting your character will explicitly be selfcast instead of attempting to target an opponent first.

### [smallcaps]{[color]{gunmetal}{Conditionals}}

Conditionals can be added and combined with target modifiers after the command within `[]` to control whether an action should take place.

All conditions within the same `[]` must be true for an action to be executed, and multiple groups of conditionals can be added for the same command.

[table]{equalcells, noborder}
[tbody]{[code]{/cast [@opponent, exists][@player] Shrink}}{Casts Shrink on your opponent, if you have an opponent. Otherwise, it casts Shrink on you}
[tbody]{[code]{/cast [@opponent, exists, @player] Shrink}}{Checks to see if you have an opponent, then changes target to yourself and casts Shrink and you}
[tbody]{[code]{/cast [@opponent, exists] Shrink}}{Casts Shrink on your opponent, if you have an opponent. Otherwise, it does nothing}
[tbody]{[code]{/cast [@player, mod:shift][@opponent] Shrink}}{Casts Shrink on yourself if the Shift key is pressed. Otherwise, attempts to cast Shrink on your opponent}
[tbody]{[code]{/cast [resting, nomod] Restore Self}}{Only attempts to cast Restore Self if you are resting and no modifier key is pressed}
[tbody]{[code]{/use [@opponent, mouse] 0}}{If the macro is triggered using mouse or touch input, will attempt to display a dropdown with use options for an opponent's head slot}

Any conditional can be prefixed with `no` to __inverse__ its condition.

Conditionals that consider a target will use the first target modifier to the left of it and default to the player's character if no target modifier has been declared.

[details]{[smallcaps]{[color]{gunmetal}{###### List of conditionals}}}{
[table]{equalcells}
[thead]{Target modifier}{Description}
[tbody]{`exists`}{True if the target was found}
[tbody]{`mindless`}{True if the target is mindless}
[tbody]{`defeated`}{True if the target has been defeated}
[tbody]{`combat`}{True if the player is in combat}
[tbody]{`resting`}{True if the player is resting}
[tbody]{`mod`[br]`mod:ctrl`[br]`mod:alt`[br]`mod:shift`}{True if the Ctrl, Alt, or Shift key is pressed[br]True if the Ctrl key is pressed[br]True if the Alt key is pressed[br]True if the Shift key is pressed}
[tbody]{`mouse`[br]`mouse:0`[br]`mouse:2`}{True if triggered by any mouse or touch input[br]True if triggered by mouse button 0 or any touch input[br]True if triggered by mouse button 2}
[tbody]{`pussy`[br]`pussy:0`}{True if the target has a Pussy Desire. A person without a vagina or the possiblity of growing a vagina won't have a Pussy Desire. Content filters and sexual preferences can affect which desires are active.}
[tbody]{`bondage:1`[br]`breasts:1`[br]`butt:1`[br]`cock:1`[br]`cum:1`[br]`mouth:1`[br]`pet:1`[br]`pussy:1`}{True if the target's Bondage Desire >= 1[br]True if the target's Breasts Desire >= 1[br]True if the target's Butt Desire >= 1[br]True if the target's Cock Desire >= 1[br]True if the target's Cum Desire >= 1[br]True if the target's Mouth Desire >= 1[br]True if the target's Pet Desire >= 1[br]True if the target's Pussy Desire >= 1}

`mouse:0` is usually the Left Mouse Button, and `mouse:2` is usually the Right Mouse Button. Any positive integer can be used in place of `0`, `1`, and `2`, and touch is only considered when `0` or no button is specified.}

### [smallcaps]{[color]{gunmetal}{Meta commands}}

[table]{equalcells, noborder}
[tbody]{[code]{#show}}{Affects the icon of a macro}
[tbody]{[code]{#showtooltip}}{Affects the icon and hover tooltip of a macro}
[tbody]{[code]{#suppresserrors}}{Prevents macro errors from being displayed}

[table]{equalcells}
[thead]{Examples}{Description}
[tbody]{`#show`[br]`#showtooltip`}{Attempts to show the spell or item of the first command following the meta command. Ignores all commands that fail their condition check}
[tbody]{`#show 0`[br]`#showtooltip 7`[br]`#showtooltip [@opponent] 0`}{Any one whole number will be treated as an equipment slot id and will show the item located in the given equipment slot. Can be used with a target modifier to show the equipped item of another player's character}
[tbody]{`#show 0 0`[br]`#showtooltip 0 5`}{Any two whole numbers will be treated as inventory coordinates and will show the item located at the given inventory coordinates}
[tbody]{`#show Breast Enlargement`[br]`#showtooltip Change Appearance: Feminine`}{Fully qualified spell names will show the given spell}
[tbody]{`#show Chromatic Dye`[br]`#showtooltip Sol Talisman`}{Base item names will show the first available item with that base. For items that stack or can be sold and bought in bulk on the item market, it will show the total number of that item in your inventory}
[tbody]{`#show Catsuit(Spell)`[br]`#showtooltip Onahole(Spell)`}{Some spells may share a name with items in your inventory. If so, you can append `(Spell)` to the name to explicitly treat the name as that of a spell. Otherwise, it will prioritize an item with the given name}
[tbody]{`#show Onahole(5159)`[br]`#showtooltip Catsuit(99239)`}{Shows a specific item with the given base name and numeric item id}
[br]
1. The icon of a macro is only altered if it uses the default `?` icon.
2. If you don't know the spell, don't have the item, or the command otherwise fails to find a target, the macro will use the default `?` icon.
3. If a valid target disappears, the macro will use a darker version of the icon for the latest known target. This could be when targeting an equipment slot, and the equipment was removed.
4. The icon for the latest known target of a macro is stored locally between sessions to prevent macros with situational targets from reverting back to the default `?` icon between sessions.
5. A macro that doesn't have the `#showtooltip` meta command will show the macro name as tooltip, if any.

###### [smallcaps]{[color]{gunmetal}{Comments}}
Any line that starts with `#` and isn't immediately followed by `show` or `showtooltip` are disregarded and can be used to write comments for a macro.

