###### [smallcaps]{[color]{gunmetal}{Run custom scripts}}

Players can use `${}` to run custom JS code inside a command and the computed value will be inserted in its place.

1. The closing and opening `{}` must appear on the same line and the code inside can only be one line.
2. The `${}` part will only run when the command is executed and cannot appear within `[]` for target modifiers and conditionals.
4. If you don't want to insert a returned value, you must make sure the returned value isn't a string or number type value.
5. You can write custom `$` properties inside `${}`, which will be kept for the duration of the login session.
6. You cannot overwrite predefined `$` properties.

[table]{equalcells, noborder}
[tbody]{[code]{`${(2 + 2) && ''}`}}{Any script between `()` will never be inserted}
[tbody]{[code]{`${$i = ($i || 0) + 1}`}}{Increments $i by one each time you run the command, and inserts the value in its place}

[color]{bronze}{Running scripts could compromise your character and cause the loss of items. You should not accept custom scripts from any source you don't trust and all attempts to run a custom script will be aborted with a warning until you allow for them to run.}

[code]{${!$i&&($c=false,$i=setInterval(()=>{let m,c=LOCATION.instance.combat;if(c!=$c)c?$t=Date.now():TEXT_LOG.instance.CombatMessage({message:`Encounter ended after ${(m=Math.floor((Date.now()-$t)/60000))?'':'<'}${m||1} minute${m>1?'s':''}`});$c=c},1000))&&''}}
Example code for a macro that starts tracking the duration of encounters when triggered and posts the duration in minutes to your combat log after an encounter ends without informing other players.

[code]{/cast Shrink ${($shrink = ($shrink || 0) + 1) && ''}
# Move line underneath to separate macro for displaying the count. 
${TEXT_LOG.instance.CombatMessage({message:`I have cast Shrink ${$shrink || 0} time${$shrink === 1 ? '' : 's'} this session`})}}
Example code for a macro that counts the number of times Shrink was cast and a second macro that writes it to your combat log without informing other players.

