### [smallcaps]{[color]{gunmetal}{Useful macros}}

[code]{#showtooltip Shrink
/cast [@opponent, exists] Shrink}
Casts a spell on your opponent if they exists. By default, spells with a target will attempt to target your opponent first, then target you if no opponent was found. This macro removes the risk of hitting yourself, and the explicit `#showtooltip Shrink` ensures the the icon and tooltip are displayed correctly for the spell, even when no valid target is found.

[code]{#showtooltip Shrink
/cast [@player, mod:shift][@opponent, exists] Shrink}
A variant of the macro above, where holding down the Shift key will cause the spell to be selfcast.

[code]{#showtooltip
/cast [resting, nomod] Restore Self
/cast [resting, mod] Soul Imprint
/cast Attack}
Restore Self and Soul Imprint can only be cast while resting, while Attack can only be used on an opponent. Since Attack is mutually exclusive to Restore Self and Soul Imprint, we can use the same macro for them and change the spell based on the situation.

[code]{#showtooltip
/cast [nocombat, nomod] Restore Self
/cast [nocombat, mod] Soul Imprint
/cast Attack}
A variant of the macro above, where Restore Self and Soul Imprint are shown instead of Attack while out of combat and not resting.

[code]{#showtooltip
/cast [@opponent, mindless, nomod] Change Name
/cast Stoke Libido}
Since Change Name can only be cast on someone else when they are mindless, while Stoke Libido becomes less useful if your oppoonent is already mindless, we can combine these spells in a single macro.

[code]{#showtooltip
/cast [@opponent, defeated, nomod] Catsuit(Spell)
/cast Smooth Skin}
Catsuit is a special action that only becomes available after you have defeated your opponent. You could combine it with another spell you prefer to use before your opponent is defeated.

[code]{#showtooltip [@opponent] 0
/use [@opponent, exists, mouse:2] 0
/cast [@opponent, exists, nomouse:2] Conjure Item 0}
A macro that displays one of your opponent's equipment slots. Clicking the macro with the Right Mouse Button will reveal a dropdown with options similar to pressing the equipment slot directly, while any other mouse, touch, and key input will open the Conjure Item screen for the equipment slot. With eight of these you could see and interact with your opponent's equipment without having to inspect them.

[code]{#showtooltip [@opponent, exists, nomod:shift][] 0
/use [@opponent, exists, mouse:2, nomod:shift][mouse:2] 0
/cast [@opponent, exists, nomouse:2, nomod:shift][nomouse:2] Conjure Item 0}
A variant of the macro above that, where your own equipment slot will be displayed and targeted while you don't have an opponent or the Shift key is pressed.

[code]{#showtooltip Cunnilingus
/cast [@opponent, exists, pussy:3] Cunnilingus
/cast [@opponent, exists, pussy:2] Finger Clit
/cast [@opponent, exists, pussy:1] Pussy Petting
/cast [@opponent, exists, pussy] Stoke Libido}
Changes what action to take based on your opponent's Pussy Desire level. The macro does nothing if your opponent doesn't have a Pussy Desire.

